# Sequence Generator Alignment (event-site-manager-service)

This service is the **active REST API**. Align with PostgreSQL `public.sequence_generator` and the SQL import pipeline in **mosc-temp**.

## Required entity pattern

```java
@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator = "sequenceGenerator")
@SequenceGenerator(
    name = "sequenceGenerator",
    sequenceName = "public.sequence_generator",
    allocationSize = 1
)
```

All entities under `src/main/java/com/eventsitemanager/domain/` must use **`allocationSize = 1`**. Do not omit it (Hibernate default = 50).

## Runtime components (this repo)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `service/SequenceSynchronizationService.java` | `setval` via static GREATEST list |
| `aop/sequence/SequenceSynchronizationAspect.java` | Duplicate PK → sync + retry |
| `web/rest/AdminController.java` | `POST /api/admin/sync-sequence` |
| `.cursor/rules/duplicate-key-prevention.mdc` | Clear `entity.setId(null)` on create |

## When adding a table

Update **together**:

1. `mosc-temp/.../Latest_Schema_Post__Blob_Claude_12.sql` end-of-file setval block
2. `mosc-temp/.../Current_Sqls/sync_sequence_after_inserts.sql`
3. `SequenceSynchronizationService.java` GREATEST list

## Post-import (every environment)

After manual INSERT seed on a database, run on **that DB**:

1. `mosc-temp/code_html_template/SQLS/Current_Sqls/sync_sequence_after_inserts.sql`
2. `sync_spring_batch_sequences.sql` if Spring Batch rows exist

Import alone does not update `sequence_generator`.

